It turned one sided. And I finally figured I had to let go. While it's not going away overnight, now I see where I am with them and need to try to move on...

That is why I am so closed off and rarely open up to people. You just get hurt. You get a very monotone wolf until I gauge how I feel with you. If I open up to you then I trust you. But to then get ignored for months into years after trying to stay connect. It hurts.

I told them straight up, I am not part of their pack. I'm a lone wolf. I don't fit into a pack. But they still pressed that I was but, again, never truly cared for. All the memories, the gifts, the art, the help given. All for nothing. That what's hurts.

I was part if their "pack" with them as "alpha", yet never checked on or cared for as a alpha would. No effect. Expects the friendship to just pick up where it left off after not talking for the longest time. Said cared for bit never shown.

Well, I guess that "friendship" has ended officially as they no longer follow me. Though I unfollowed them a bit ago to see what happens. The result was expected, an unfollow and radio silence. *sigh* All the devotion to that friendship for years, nothing returned...
